美國的'''聯邦醫療補助'''（{{lang-en|Medicaid}}）是一項由聯邦和州共同提供經費的[[醫療衛生|醫療衛生]]計劃，目的是為某些收入和資源有限的人所提供的醫療費用協助。Medicaid還提供通常[[聯邦醫療保險|聯邦醫療保險]]（Medicare）並未涵蓋的福利，包括療養院護理和個人護理服務。這兩個計劃之間的主要區別在於Medicaid計劃為低收入人群支付醫療費用，而Medicare計劃為老年人提供[[醫療保險|醫療保險]]。對於能同時享有Medicaid和Medicare的人，還有{{le|Medicare雙重合格|Medicare dual eligible}}計劃。<ref>{{cite web |title=Medicare & Medicaid |url=https://www.hhs.gov/answers/medicare-and-medicaid/index.html |website=HHS.gov U.S. Department of Health & Human Services |access-date=17 February 2021 |archive-date=2021-05-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210501024814/https://www.hhs.gov/answers/medicare-and-medicaid/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>美國醫療保險協會（Health Insurance Association of America）把Medicaid描述為"政府所提供，針對收入和資源不足的人士，而不論他們年齡的醫療保險計劃。"<ref>[[America's_Health_Insurance_Plans|America's Health Insurance Plans]] (HIAA), p. 232</ref>

==概論==
Medicaid是美國低收入人群醫療衛生相關服務的最大經費來源，截至2017年，這種免費服務為7,400萬低收入和殘疾人士（占美國人口的23％）提供醫療保險涵蓋，<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=http://econofact.org/evidence-on-the-value-of-medicaid|title=Evidence on the Value of Medicaid|last=Gottlieb|first=Joshua D.|last2=Shepard|first2=Mark|name-list-format=vanc|date=2017-07-02|work=Econofact|access-date=2017-07-05|archive-date=2017-07-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170703153212/http://econofact.org/evidence-on-the-value-of-medicaid|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=NPR_Medicaid >{{cite news | last=Terhune | first=Chad | date=2018-10-18 | title=Private Medicaid Plans Receive Billions In Tax Dollars, With Little Oversight | url=https://www.npr.org/sections/health-shots/2018/10/18/657862337/private-medicaid-plans-receive-billions-in-tax-dollars-with-little-oversight | department=Health Shots | publisher=[[NPR|NPR]] | accessdate=2018-10-18 | quote=...Medicaid, the nation's public insurance program that assists 75 million low-income Americans. | archive-date=2018-10-18 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181018134145/https://www.npr.org/sections/health-shots/2018/10/18/657862337/private-medicaid-plans-receive-billions-in-tax-dollars-with-little-oversight | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=US-Pop>{{cite report | title=Annual Estimates of the Resident Population: April 1, 2010 to July 1, 2017 | url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/PEP/2017/PEPANNRES/0100000US | accessdate=2018-10-18 | publisher=United States Census Bureau, Population Division | date=2017-12-01 | quote=Estimated United States population as of July 1, 2017 = 325,719,178 | archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213010033/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/PEP/2017/PEPANNRES/0100000US | archivedate=2020-02-13 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>以及負擔2019年美國半數的接生費用。<ref name="Franco"/>這個保險計劃的受保人需要經過[[經濟狀況調查|經濟狀況調查]]，由州和聯邦政府共同提供經費，管理則由州政府負責，<ref name=":3" />美國各州都有很大的空間來決定誰有資格接受補助。截至2017年，Medicaid的年度總成本剛超過6,000億美元，其中聯邦政府提供3,750億美元，其餘的2,300億美元則由各州提供。<ref name="Franco" />各州並非受到強制來參與這項計劃，但從1982年以來，所有的州都已加入。受益者必須是美國公民，或者是有資格的非公民，包括低收入的成年人、其子女、和有某些殘障的人士。<ref>{{cite web |title=Coverage for lawfully present immigrants |url=https://www.healthcare.gov/immigrants/lawfully-present-immigrants/ |publisher=Healthcare.gov |accessdate=2019-01-09 |archive-date=2019-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190118002123/https://www.healthcare.gov/immigrants/lawfully-present-immigrants/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

《[[患者保護與平價醫療法案|患者保護與平價醫療法案]]》（PPACA，或稱ACA）把Medicaid的資格，以及聯邦的撥款都大幅擴張。根據這項法案，所有收入不超過貧窮標線 133％的美國公民，以及有資格的非公民，包括無受撫養子女的成年人，只要住在參與Medicaid擴張（或稱擴大，擴展，Medicaid Expansion） 的州，都可受到覆蓋。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Medicaid, Children's Health Insurance Program, & Basic Health Program Eligibility Levels {{!}} Medicaid|url=https://www.medicaid.gov/medicaid/national-medicaid-chip-program-information/medicaid-childrens-health-insurance-program-basic-health-program-eligibility-levels/index.html|access-date=2021-02-14|website=www.medicaid.gov|archive-date=2021-04-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210418165934/https://www.medicaid.gov/medicaid/national-medicaid-chip-program-information/medicaid-childrens-health-insurance-program-basic-health-program-eligibility-levels/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>但是[[美國最高法院|美國最高法院]]在“[[全國獨立企業聯盟訴西貝利厄斯案|全國獨立企業聯盟訴西貝利厄斯案]]”中判定，各州不必同意參與這一擴張才能繼續獲得以前即已確定的Medicaid經費，有些州選擇不參與擴張，仍維持PPACA之前的經費水準，還有維持州民原有的資格標準。<ref name=":4">{{Cite web|url=https://www.medicaid.gov/affordable-care-act/eligibility/index.html|title=Eligibility|website=www.medicaid.gov|language=en-us|access-date=2018-04-12|archive-date=2018-04-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180402140423/https://www.medicaid.gov/affordable-care-act/eligibility/index.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

研究顯示，Medicaid計劃把醫療保險的覆蓋、服務的取得、受惠者的財務、以及某些健康結果，都做出改善，也提供經濟利益給各州和[[醫療衛生提供者|醫療衛生提供者]]。<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":7">{{Cite web|url=https://www.kff.org/medicaid/issue-brief/the-effects-of-medicaid-expansion-under-the-aca-updated-findings-from-a-literature-review-august-2019/|title=The Effects of Medicaid Expansion under the ACA: Updated Findings from a Literature Review|last1=Antonisse|first1=Larisa|last2=Aug 15|first2=Madeline Guth Published|date=2019-08-15|website=The Henry J. Kaiser Family Foundation|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-26|last3=2019|archive-date=2019-09-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190926093449/https://www.kff.org/medicaid/issue-brief/the-effects-of-medicaid-expansion-under-the-aca-updated-findings-from-a-literature-review-august-2019/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The evidence on Medicaid expansion|publisher=American Medical Association|url=https://www.ama-assn.org/system/files/2020-10/research-summary-benefits-of-medicaid-expansion.pdf|access-date=2021-02-27|archive-date=2021-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210331022828/https://www.ama-assn.org/system/files/2020-10/research-summary-benefits-of-medicaid-expansion.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
Medicaid、Medicare、{{link-en|軍人醫療保險|TRicare}}、和軍人眷屬醫療保險（Federal benefits for veterans, dependents and survivors，ChampVA）是由美國政府提供經費的四項醫療保險計劃，前兩項的管理是由位在[[馬里蘭州|馬里蘭州]][[巴爾的摩|巴爾的摩]]市的{{link-en|聯邦醫療保險和聯邦醫療補助服務中心|Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services}}（CMS）負責。<ref name="official">{{cite web|url=https://www.medicare.gov/about-us/about-medicare.html|title=About Medicare|website=www.medicare.gov|publisher=U.S. Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services in Baltimore|access-date=2017-10-25|archive-date=2017-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171023124013/https://www.medicare.gov/about-us/about-medicare.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>
