==利用率==
在2003年至2012年的期間，由Medicaid付費的患者住院次數增加2.5％，即80萬人次。<ref>{{cite web |vauthors=Wiess AJ, Elixhauser A |title=Overview of Hospital Utilization, 2012 |work=HCUP Statistical Brief #180 |publisher=Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality |location=Rockville, MD |date=October 2014 |url=https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/reports/statbriefs/sb179-Emergency-Department-Trends.jsp |accessdate=2020-07-26 |archive-date=2014-12-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141224224220/https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/reports/statbriefs/sb179-Emergency-Department-Trends.jsp |dead-url=no }}</ref>在2019年，美國有一半的嬰兒接生由Medicaid負擔費用。
 
Medicaid的超級利用者（定義為一年內入院4次或以上的患者）佔了大部分的住院次數（5.9次對1.3次），住院時間更長（6.1天對4.5天），以及每次更高的住院費用（11,766美元對9,032美元）。<ref name="Characteristics of Hospital Stays">{{cite web |vauthors=Jiang HJ, Barrett ML, Sheng M |title=Characteristics of Hospital Stays for Nonelderly Medicaid Super-Utilizers, 2012 |work=HCUP Statistical Brief #184 |publisher=Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality |location=Rockville, MD |date=November 2014 |url=https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/reports/statbriefs/sb184-Hospital-Stays-Medicaid-Super-Utilizers-2012.jsp |accessdate=2020-07-26 |archive-date=2015-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411224657/https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/reports/statbriefs/sb184-Hospital-Stays-Medicaid-Super-Utilizers-2012.jsp |dead-url=yes }}</ref> Medicaid super-utilizers were more likely than other Medicaid patients to be male and to be aged 45–64 years.<ref name="Characteristics of Hospital Stays" />

這種超級利用者通常是男性，年齡在45歲到64歲之間。<ref name="Characteristics of Hospital Stays" />他們的常見疾病包括[[情感障礙|情緒障礙]]和[[精神疾患|精神疾患]]、以及[[糖尿病|糖尿病]]、[[癌症|癌症]]、[[鐮刀型紅血球疾病|鐮刀型紅血球疾病]]、[[敗血症|敗血症]]、鬱血性[[心臟衰竭|心臟衰竭]]、[[慢性阻塞性肺病|慢性阻塞性肺病]]、體內義體裝置物及移植物所致之併發症。<ref name="Characteristics of Hospital Stays" />

==預算與財務==
[[File:U.S._healthcare_GDP.gif|frame]]（公共和私人總和）中的佔比，在GDP中的佔比圖，資料來源：{{le|美國國會預算辦公室|congress budget office}}<ref>[http://www.cbo.gov/ftpdocs/87xx/doc8758/MainText.3.1.shtml#1077141 The Long-Term Outlook for Health Care Spending] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cbo.gov/ftpdocs/87xx/doc8758/MainText.3.1.shtml#1077141 |date=20120126173451 }}. Figure 2. [[Congressional_Budget_Office|Congressional Budget Office]].</ref>]]

Medicaid是聯邦與州的聯合計劃，與純粹由聯邦提供經費的Medicare不同。每個州都有自己的Medicaid管理系統，但系統必須符合聯邦準則的規定，以便從聯邦獲得匹配的經費和捐贈。[[美屬薩摩亞|美屬薩摩亞]]、[[波多黎各|波多黎各]]、[[關島|關島]]、和[[美屬維爾京群島|美屬維爾京群島]]則完全是由聯邦提供經費。<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.dcreport.org/2019/06/11/puerto-ricos-post-maria-medicaid-crisis/|title = Puerto Rico's Post-Maria Medicaid Crisis|date = 2019-06-11|accessdate = 2020-07-26|archive-date = 2020-08-03|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200803212348/https://www.dcreport.org/2019/06/11/puerto-ricos-post-maria-medicaid-crisis/|dead-url = yes}}</ref>提供給各州的匹配率是使用聯邦匹配公式（稱為{{link-en|聯邦醫療協助百分比|Federal Medical Assistance Percentages}}）來確定，公式產生的撥款率因州而異，由每個州的人均收入來決定。<ref>[http://www.ssa.gov/OP_Home/ssact/title11/1101.htm SSA.gov] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ssa.gov/OP_Home/ssact/title11/1101.htm |date=20200717161552 }}, Social Security Act. Title IX, Sec. 1101(a)(8)(B)</ref>最富裕的州只得到50％的匹配撥款，而比較貧窮的州則分得較高比率的匹配撥款。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Mitchell|first1=Alison|title=Medicaid's Federal Medical Assistance Percentage (FMAP)|date=2018-04-25|publisher=Congressional Research Service|location=Washington, DC|url=https://fas.org/sgp/crs/misc/R43847.pdf|access-date=2018-05-05|archive-date=2018-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180605230445/https://fas.org/sgp/crs/misc/R43847.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
在過去幾年中，Medicaid的經費已成為許多州的重大預算問題，平均每州在這個計劃上的花費，佔一般預算的16.8％。如果把聯邦匹配經費計入，平均將佔到每個州預算的22％。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nasbo.org/Publications/PDFs/Fiscal%20Survey%20of%20the%20States%20June%202007.pdf|title=Microsoft Word – Final Text.doc<!-- Bot generated title -->|website=nasbo.org|access-date=2007-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071127095746/http://www.nasbo.org/Publications/PDFs/Fiscal%20Survey%20of%20the%20States%20June%202007.pdf|archive-date=2007-11-27|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>[http://ccf.georgetown.edu/index/medicaid-and-state-budgets-looking-at-the-facts "Medicaid and State Budgets: Looking at the Facts"] {{Wayback|url=http://ccf.georgetown.edu/index/medicaid-and-state-budgets-looking-at-the-facts |date=20080725043958 }}, Georgetown University Center for Children and Families, May 2008.</ref>2004年，大約有4,300萬美國人受到Medicaid的覆蓋（其中1,970萬為兒童），總費用為2,950億美元。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbpp.org/cms/index.cfm?fa=view&id=2223|title=Policy Basics: Introduction to Medicaid|date=2009-01-06|accessdate=2020-07-26|archive-date=2015-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150320140552/http://www.cbpp.org/cms/index.cfm?fa=view&id=2223|dead-url=no}}</ref>2008年，Medicaid計劃提供醫療保險和服務給大約4,900萬低收入兒童、孕婦、老年人、和殘疾人士。<ref>{{cite book |last= |first= |author-link= |date= |title= US National Educational and Social Development Policy Handbook Volume 2|url= https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=MEs6CgAAQBAJ&pg=PA58&lpg=PA58&dq=In+2008,+Medicaid+provided+health+coverage+and+services+to+approximately+49+million+low-income+children,+pregnant+women,+elderly+people,+and+disabled+people.&source=bl&ots=6Qr4tUhvP6&sig=ACfU3U2cLtTYYkDb3LK3XU-rzDJpPAC1TQ&hl=zh-TW&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiUkaesvIfvAhWNGaYKHYcXCSIQ6AEwAnoECAgQAw#v=onepage&q=In%202008%2C%20Medicaid%20provided%20health%20coverage%20and%20services%20to%20approximately%2049%20million%20low-income%20children%2C%20pregnant%20women%2C%20elderly%20people%2C%20and%20disabled%20people.&f=false|location= |publisher= IBP, Inc.|page= 58|isbn=}}</ref>2008年的Medicaid計劃的支出估計為 2,040億美元。<ref>[http://www.whitehouse.gov/omb/budget/fy2008/hhs.html "Budget of the United States Government, FY 2008"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.whitehouse.gov/omb/budget/fy2008/hhs.html |date=20090515152348 }}, Department of Health and Human Services, 2008.</ref>2011年，有760萬例住院醫療費用由Medicaid支付，占美國住院患者費用的15.6％（約合602億美元）。<ref>Torio CM, Andrews RM. National Inpatient Hospital Costs: The Most Expensive Conditions by Payer, 2011. HCUP Statistical Brief #160. Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality, Rockville, MD. August 2013. [http://hcup-us.ahrq.gov/reports/statbriefs/sb160.jsp] {{Wayback|url=http://hcup-us.ahrq.gov/reports/statbriefs/sb160.jsp |date=20170314171958 }}</ref>Medicaid計劃負擔的平均每次住院費用[[中位數|中位數]]為8,000美元，比全國的平均住院費用少2,000美元。<ref>{{cite web |vauthors=Pfuntner A, Wier LM, Steiner C |title=Costs for Hospital Stays in the United States, 2011. |work=HCUP Statistical Brief #168 |publisher=Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality |location=Rockville, MD |date=December 2013 |url=http://hcup-us.ahrq.gov/reports/statbriefs/sb168-Hospital-Costs-United-States-2011.jsp |accessdate=2020-07-26 |archive-date=2020-07-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200729154431/https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/reports/statbriefs/sb168-Hospital-Costs-United-States-2011.jsp |dead-url=yes }}</ref>
 
2014年的Medicaid計劃的實際支出為4,963億美元。聯邦支出佔3,015億美元（佔比61%），各州總共支出佔1,948億美元（佔比39%）<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cms.gov/research-statistics-data-and-systems/research/actuarialstudies/downloads/medicaidreport2015.pdf |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2020-07-26 |archive-date=2019-09-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190907022338/https://www.cms.gov/Research-Statistics-Data-and-Systems/Research/ActuarialStudies/Downloads/MedicaidReport2015.pdf |dead-url=yes }}</ref>Medicaid不會直接直接付款給個人；而是撥付給醫療機構。在某些州，Medicaid受益人自己需要支付一小筆費用（共付額）。<ref name=":4" />根據聯邦法律Medicaid覆蓋適用的範圍僅限於 "必要的醫療服務"（請參考[[醫療必要性|醫療必要性]]）。<ref name="Adler">{{cite journal | vauthors = Adler PW | title = Is it lawful to use Medicaid to pay for circumcision? | journal = Journal of Law and Medicine | volume = 19 | issue = 2 | pages = 335–53 | date = December 2011 | pmid = 22320007 | url = http://www.doctorsopposingcircumcision.org/pdf/2011-12_Adler.pdf | access-date = 2012-04-30 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141129090312/http://www.doctorsopposingcircumcision.org/pdf/2011-12_Adler.pdf | archive-date = 2014-11-29 | dead-url = yes }}</ref>

Medicaid計劃在1965年被制定，其中有條款"對接受Medicaid福利時超過65歲的受益者，他們過世後，如果沒有尚存的配偶，沒有未成年子女，或者成年但有殘疾的子女，各州得透過法律途徑追討遺產來回收費用。" <ref name="Kiely">Eugene Kiely, [http://www.factcheck.org/2014/01/medicaid-estate-recovery-program/ Medicaid Estate Recovery Program] {{Wayback|url=http://www.factcheck.org/2014/01/medicaid-estate-recovery-program/ |date=20191129160749 }}, [[FactCheck.org|FactCheck.org]], [[Annenberg_Public_Policy_Center|Annenberg Public Policy Center]], University of Pennsylvania (January 10, 2014).</ref>1993年，國會頒布《{{le|1993年綜合預算調節法|Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act of 1993}}》，其中要求各州盡力追討"55歲或以上已故Medicaid受益者的長期護理和相關費用." <ref name="Kiely"/>這項法案還允許各州自行決定是否追討那些已故受益人的其他Medicaid費用。<ref name="Kiely"/> 但是，如果過世的受益人"有尚存的配偶，21歲以下子女，或不論年紀的的盲人或殘障子女"和"法律還為逝者的成年子女提供例外條例，如果子女是賺錢養家活口的、財產由兄弟姐妹共有、以及諸如農場之類的創造收益中的財產。"法律禁止追討這類遺產 <ref name="Kiely"/>目前每州都有Medicaid財產追回計劃，所收回的款項因州而異，"取決於各州執行的方法，還有執行時使用的力道。"<ref name="Kiely"/>
 
2008年11月25日，有一項新的聯邦法規通過，允許各州向參與Medicaid計劃的人收取保費和較高的共付額。<ref>[http://www.gpoaccess.gov/fr/ search: 42 CFR Parts 447 and 457] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120310235019/http://www.gpoaccess.gov/fr/ |date=2012-03-10 }}</ref>這項法規讓各州獲得更多收入，而能降低計劃的財務壓力。據估計，各州的節省可達11億美元，而聯邦政府可節省近 14億美元。但是，這意味著那些1,300萬Medicaid受益者必須承擔這種財務負擔，他們在5年內的共付款會增加13億美元。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/27/us/27medicaid.html?_r=1&scp=2&sq=medicaid&st=cse |work=The New York Times |first=Robert |last=Pear |title=New Medicaid Rules Allow States to Set Premiums and Higher Co-Payments |date=2008-11-27 |accessdate=2020-07-26 |archive-date=2020-07-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718145732/https://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/27/us/27medicaid.html?_r=1&scp=2&sq=medicaid&st=cse |dead-url=no }}</ref>讓人關注的是，這樣的法規會抑制低收入人群去尋求醫療衛生服務。直到參與者在病情嚴重的時候才被迫支付增加的費用去接受治療，目前尚不清楚這項法規會產生什麼樣的長期影響。

2019年所做的的一項研究發現，[[密歇根州|密歇根州]]的Medicaid計劃擴張對該州產生淨的正面財政影響。<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Levy|first=Helen|last2=Ayanian|first2=John Z.|last3=Buchmueller|first3=Thomas C.|last4=Grimes|first4=Donald R.|last5=Ehrlich|first5=Gabriel|title=Macroeconomic Feedback Effects of Medicaid Expansion: Evidence from Michigan|journal=Journal of Health Politics, Policy and Law|volume=45|pages=5–48|language=en|doi=10.1215/03616878-7893555|pmid=31675091|year=2020|doi-access=free}}</ref>

==效果==
凱撒家庭基金會在2019年對324項有關Medicaid Expansion作總結研究，結論是："Medicaid Expansion與覆蓋率的提高、獲得醫療機會的改善、財務安全增進、某些健康狀況/結果衡量指標的改進、以及州和醫療機構獲得經濟效益，都有關聯。"<ref name=":7" />
 
一項在2021年所做的研究發現，Medicaid擴張導致死亡率大幅降低，主要是由與疾病相關的死亡人數的減少所致。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Miller|first1=Sarah|last2=Johnson|first2=Norman|last3=Wherry|first3=Laura R|date=2021-01-30|title=Medicaid and Mortality: New Evidence from Linked Survey and Administrative Data*|url=https://doi.org/10.1093/qje/qjab004|journal=The Quarterly Journal of Economics|doi=10.1093/qje/qjab004|issn=0033-5533}}</ref>《{{le|政治經濟學雜誌Journal of Political Economy}}》在2018年所做的研究發現，Medicaid一經推出後，便在1960年代和1970年代把嬰兒和兒童死亡率降低。<ref name=":2">{{cite journal |last1=Goodman-Bacon |first1=Andrew |title=Public Insurance and Mortality: Evidence from Medicaid Implementation |journal=Journal of Political Economy |date=February 2018 |volume=126 |issue=1 |pages=216–262 |doi=10.1086/695528 |s2cid=158783532 |url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~ajgb/medicaid_ajgb.pdf |access-date=2020-07-26 |archive-date=2019-12-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191212175938/http://www-personal.umich.edu/~ajgb/medicaid_ajgb.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>非白人兒童的死亡率下降尤為顯著。<ref name=":2" />《{{le|美國公共衛生雜誌|eAmerican Journal of Public Health}}》於2018年進行的一項研究發現，採取Medicaid擴張的州，嬰兒死亡率下降，而拒絕參與的州則結果相反。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Bhatt |first1=Chintan B. |last2=Beck-Sagué |first2=Consuelo M. |title=Medicaid Expansion and Infant Mortality in the United States |journal=American Journal of Public Health |date=April 2018 |volume=108 |issue=4 |pages=565–7 |pmid=29346003 |pmc=5844390 |doi=10.2105/ajph.2017.304218 }}</ref>一項在2020年[[美國醫學會雜誌|美國醫學會雜誌]]所做的研究發現，Medicaid擴張與晚期[[乳癌|乳癌]]的發生率降低相關，表明Medicaid的容易獲得導致乳腺癌的早期發現，和提高存活率。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Blanc|first1=Justin M. Le|last2=Heller|first2=Danielle R.|last3=Friedrich|first3=Ann|last4=Lannin|first4=Donald R.|last5=Park|first5=Tristen S.|date=2020-07-01|title=Association of Medicaid Expansion Under the Affordable Care Act With Breast Cancer Stage at Diagnosis|url=https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jamasurgery/fullarticle/2767686|journal=JAMA Surgery|language=en|volume=155|issue=8|page=752|doi=10.1001/jamasurg.2020.1495|pmc=7330827|pmid=32609338|pmc-embargo-date=July 1, 2021}}</ref>一項在2020年所做的研究發現，沒有證據表明Medicaid擴張會對醫療保險接受者的醫療品質產生不利影響。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Carey|first1=Colleen M.|last2=Miller|first2=Sarah|last3=Wherry|first3=Laura R.|date=2020|title=The Impact of Insurance Expansions on the Already Insured: The Affordable Care Act and Medicare|url=https://www.aeaweb.org/articles?id=10.1257/app.20190176|journal=American Economic Journal: Applied Economics|language=en|volume=12|issue=4|pages=288–318|doi=10.1257/app.20190176|issn=1945-7782|access-date=2022-03-03|archive-date=2021-04-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423074355/https://www.aeaweb.org/articles?id=10.1257%2Fapp.20190176|dead-url=no}}</ref>一項在2018年的研究發現，在2000年代初期，Medicaid計劃在[[紐約州|紐約州]]、亞利桑那州、和緬因州的擴張導致死亡率下降6％："與HIV相關死亡率（受最近引入的抗逆轉錄病毒藥物的影響）的影響佔20％ 。死亡率的變化與縣級保險覆蓋率的提高緊密相關，每年為每239至316名獲得保險的成年人挽救一條生命，顯示每條生命的成本節省在327,000美元至867,000美元之間，與大多數生命價值統計的估計作比較，屬於有利。"<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Sommers|first1=Benjamin D.|date=July 2017|title=State Medicaid Expansions and Mortality, Revisited: A Cost-Benefit Analysis|url=https://dash.harvard.edu/bitstream/1/27305958/1/Mcaid%20Mortality%20Revisited%20DASH%20Version.pdf|journal=American Journal of Health Economics|volume=3|issue=3|pages=392–421|doi=10.1162/ajhe_a_00080|s2cid=53488456}}</ref>

在2016年，有一篇論文發現Medicaid對受益者的健康具有長遠,正面的影響："對幼兒提供Medicaid可降低死亡率和殘疾發生率，並且對於白人來說，可增加邊際勞動力的供應，並減少往後50年內的殘疾現金補助計劃，和公共醫療保險的支出。受益者的總收入不會改變，因為殘障福利被收入替代。"<ref name=":0">{{cite journal |last1=Goodman-Bacon |first1=Andrew |title=The Long-Run Effects of Childhood Insurance Coverage: Medicaid Implementation, Adult Health, and Labor Market Outcomes |journal=NBER Working Paper |date=December 2016 |pages=22899 |url=https://www.nber.org/papers/w22899 |publisher=National Bureau of Economic Research |doi=10.3386/w22899 |doi-access=free |access-date=2020-07-26 |archive-date=2020-07-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200717142109/https://www.nber.org/papers/w22899 |dead-url=no }}</ref>因為Medicaid的受益者更為健康的緣故，政府可在日後的福利支出的節省和增加稅收把用在Medicaid的投資給收回："政府對這些兒童的原始投資，可獲得的年度折現回報率達到 2%-7%之間，其中大部分的回報是來自將來較低的現金補助支出。" <ref name=":0" />NBER在2019年發表的一篇論文發現，當[[夏威夷州|夏威夷州]]停止允許[[自由聯合協定|自由聯合協定]]（COFA）移民參加該州的Medicaid計劃時，這類人群的Medicaid資助的住院人數下降69％，急診室就診人數下降42％ ，但是沒有保險覆蓋的急診次數增加，由Medicaid資助的嬰兒急診次數也大幅增加。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Halliday|first1=Timothy J|last2=Akee|first2=Randall Q|last3=Sentell|first3=Tetine|last4=Inada|first4=Megan|last5=Miyamura|first5=Jill|date=2019|title=The Impact of Medicaid on Medical Utilization in a Vulnerable Population: Evidence from COFA Migrants|url=http://www.nber.org/papers/w26030|doi=10.3386/w26030|hdl-access=free|hdl=10419/215175|s2cid=198255625|journal=|access-date=2020-07-26|archive-date=2020-08-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200802103109/https://www.nber.org/papers/w26030|dead-url=no}}</ref>NBER的另一篇論文發現，Medicaid擴張把死亡率降低。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Miller|first1=Sarah|last2=Altekruse|first2=Sean|last3=Johnson|first3=Norman|last4=Wherry|first4=Laura R|date=2019|title=Medicaid and Mortality: New Evidence from Linked Survey and Administrative Data|url=http://www.nber.org/papers/w26081|doi=10.3386/w26081|s2cid=164463149|journal=|access-date=2020-07-26|archive-date=2020-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200727020737/https://www.nber.org/papers/w26081|dead-url=no}}</ref>

一項在2020年的研究發現，Medicaid擴張把鄉村醫院的收入和營業利潤率提高，對小型城市醫院沒有影響，並導致大型城市醫院的收入下降。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Moghtaderi|first1=Ali|last2=Pines|first2=Jesse|last3=Zocchi|first3=Mark|last4=Black|first4=Bernard|date=2020|title=The effect of Affordable Care Act Medicaid expansion on hospital revenue|url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1002/hec.4157|journal=Health Economics|language=en|volume=29|issue=12|pages=1682–1704|doi=10.1002/hec.4157|issn=1099-1050|pmid=32935892|access-date=2021-02-27|archive-date=2020-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030152736/https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1002/hec.4157|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[史丹佛大學|史丹佛大學]]和[[賓夕法尼亞大學沃頓商學院|賓夕法尼亞大學沃頓商學院]]的經濟學家們在2019年發表的一篇論文說，Medicaid Expansion"讓醫院的收入和利潤大幅增加，政府醫院獲得相當良好的收益。在民眾福利方面，我們沒察覺出民眾的健康有明顯的改進，但是擴張導致醫院和急診室的使用大增，並把護理從公立醫院移轉到私人的，品質更好的醫院。" <ref>{{cite journal |last1=Duggan |first1=Mark |last2=Gupta |first2=Atul |last3=Jackson |first3=Emilie |title=The Impact of the Affordable Care Act: Evidence from California's Hospital Sector |journal=NBER Working Paper |date=2019 |pages=25488 |url=http://www.nber.org/papers/w25488 |publisher=National Bureau of Economic Research |doi=10.3386/w25488 |access-date=2020-07-26 |archive-date=2020-07-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718225711/https://www.nber.org/papers/w25488 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2017年對Medicaid計劃的學術研究所做的調查發現，計劃把接受者的健康和財務安全改善。<ref name=":1" />研究顯示Medicaid Expansion與就業人數的增加和入學人數的增加都有關聯。<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Tipirneni|first=Renuka|last2=Ayanian|first2=John Z.|last3=Patel|first3=Minal R.|last4=Kieffer|first4=Edith C.|last5=Kirch|first5=Matthias A.|last6=Bryant|first6=Corey|last7=Kullgren|first7=Jeffrey T.|last8=Clark|first8=Sarah J.|last9=Lee|first9=Sunghee|last10=Solway|first10=Erica|last11=Chang|first11=Tammy|date=2020-01-03|title=Association of Medicaid Expansion With Enrollee Employment and Student Status in Michigan|journal=JAMA Network Open|language=en|volume=3|issue=1|pages=e1920316|doi=10.1001/jamanetworkopen.2019.20316|pmid=32003820|doi-access=free}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Hall|first=Jean P.|last2=Shartzer|first2=Adele|last3=Kurth|first3=Noelle K.|last4=Thomas|first4=Kathleen C.|date=2018-07-19|title=Medicaid Expansion as an Employment Incentive Program for People With Disabilities|journal=American Journal of Public Health|volume=108|issue=9|pages=1235–1237|doi=10.2105/AJPH.2018.304536|issn=0090-0036|pmc=6085052|pmid=30024794}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Hall|first=Jean P.|last2=Shartzer|first2=Adele|last3=Kurth|first3=Noelle K.|last4=Thomas|first4=Kathleen C.|date=2016-12-20|title=Effect of Medicaid Expansion on Workforce Participation for People With Disabilities|journal=American Journal of Public Health|volume=107|issue=2|pages=262–264|doi=10.2105/AJPH.2016.303543|issn=0090-0036|pmc=5227925|pmid=27997244}}</ref>2017年的一篇論文發現，Medicaid擴張計劃"在頭兩年把未付醫療帳單催收回來34億美元，並防止新的拖欠，而且把患者的信用評分提高。我們運用患者的信用報價和定價數據，由於家庭財務狀況改善，讓每年有5.2億美元的信貸條件改善。這樣計算出來的結果，除了直接減少[[自付費用|自付費用]]外，再把這些間接收益列入考慮，Medicaid的經濟收益等於是翻了一倍。"<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Brevoort|first1=Kenneth|last2=Grodzicki|first2=Daniel|last3=Hackmann|first3=Martin B|date=November 2017|title=Medicaid and Financial Health|url=https://www.nber.org/papers/w24002|journal=NBER Working Paper|publisher=National Bureau of Economic Research|pages=24002|doi=10.3386/w24002|doi-access=free|access-date=2020-07-26|archive-date=2020-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200728153111/https://www.nber.org/papers/w24002|dead-url=no}}</ref>研究發現，Medicaid擴張減少某些州的貧困率和嚴重的[[糧食安全|糧食安全]]狀況。<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Zewde|first1=Naomi|last2=Wimer|first2=Christopher|date=January 2019|title=Antipoverty Impact Of Medicaid Growing With State Expansions Over Time|journal=Health Affairs|volume=38|issue=1|pages=132–138|doi=10.1377/hlthaff.2018.05155|pmid=30615519}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Himmelstein|first=Gracie|date=2019-07-18|title=Effect of the Affordable Care Act's Medicaid Expansions on Food Security, 2010–2016|journal=American Journal of Public Health|volume=109|issue=9|pages=e1–e6|doi=10.2105/AJPH.2019.305168|issn=0090-0036|pmc=6687269|pmid=31318597}}</ref>而對阿肯色州施行Medicaid工作要求（Medicaid Work Requirement）所做的研究發現，這種做法導致無保險覆蓋的人數增加、醫療債務增加、尋求醫療和服藥的延遲，而對就業率並無顯著影響。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/science/la-sci-arkansas-medicaid-work-requirements-backfire-20190619-story.html|title=Arkansas' Medicaid work requirement left people uninsured without boosting employment|last=Galewitz|first=Phil|website=latimes.com|access-date=2019-06-22|date=June 19, 2019|archive-date=2019-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190622110443/https://www.latimes.com/science/la-sci-arkansas-medicaid-work-requirements-backfire-20190619-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Sommers|first1=Benjamin D.|last2=Goldman|first2=Anna L.|last3=Blendon|first3=Robert J.|last4=Orav|first4=E. John|last5=Epstein|first5=Arnold M.|date=2019-06-19|title=Medicaid Work Requirements — Results from the First Year in Arkansas|journal=New England Journal of Medicine|volume=381|issue=11|pages=1073–1082|doi=10.1056/NEJMsr1901772|pmid=31216419|issn=0028-4793|doi-access=free}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|date=2020|title=Medicaid Work Requirements In Arkansas: Two-Year Impacts On Coverage, Employment, And Affordability Of Care|url=https://doi.org/10.1377/hlthaff.2020.00538|journal=Health Affairs|doi=10.1377/hlthaff.2020.00538|last1=Sommers|first1=Benjamin D.|last2=Chen|first2=Lucy|last3=Blendon|first3=Robert J.|last4=Orav|first4=E. John|last5=Epstein|first5=Arnold M.|volume=39|issue=9|pages=1522–1530|pmid=32897784|pmc=7497731|pmc-embargo-date=September 1, 2021}}</ref>

在2017年的一項研究發現，Medicaid計劃的收益者的政治參與度增加（根據選民登記和投票率作衡量）。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Clinton |first1=Joshua D. |last2=Sances |first2=Michael W. |title=The Politics of Policy: The Initial Mass Political Effects of Medicaid Expansion in the States |journal=American Political Science Review |date=2017-11-02 |volume=112 |issue=1 |pages=167–185 |doi=10.1017/S0003055417000430 }}</ref>
 
研究發現，Medicaid擴張減少犯罪。推測減少機制是由於Medicaid把個人的經濟安全提高，並為{{le|物質濫用預防|Substance abuse prevention}}或{{le|行為障礙疾患提|Emotional and behavioral disorders}}提供更多的治療途徑。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=He|first1=Qiwei|last2=Barkowski|first2=Scott|date=2020|title=The effect of health insurance on crime: Evidence from the Affordable Care Act Medicaid expansion|url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1002/hec.3977|journal=Health Economics|language=en|volume=29|issue=3|pages=261–277|doi=10.1002/hec.3977|issn=1099-1050|pmid=31908077|access-date=2021-02-27|archive-date=2020-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200503034652/https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1002/hec.3977|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Wen|first1=Hefei|last2=Hockenberry|first2=Jason M.|last3=Cummings|first3=Janet R.|date=October 2017|title=The effect of Medicaid expansion on crime reduction: Evidence from HIFA-waiver expansions|journal=Journal of Public Economics|volume=154|pages=67–94|doi=10.1016/j.jpubeco.2017.09.001}}</ref>

===俄勒岡州Medicaid計劃健康實驗和爭議===
{{main|{{link-en|俄勒岡Medicaid計劃健康實驗|Oregon Medicaid health experiment}}}}

2008年，俄勒岡州決定為Medicaid計劃辦理一次調查，利用隨機方式選出10,000名有資格獲得Medicaid覆蓋的低收入人群，來衡量醫療保險對他們健康的影響，隨機抽樣可避免樣本有潛在的{{link-en|選擇偏差|selection bias}}。

由[[麻省理工學院|麻省理工學院]]和{{link-en|哈佛大學公共衛生學院|Harvard T.H. Chan School of Public Health}}所做的兩項引人注目的隨機抽樣研究結果<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Baicker|first=Katherine|last2=Taubman|first2=Sarah L.|last3=Allen|first3=Heidi L.|last4=Bernstein|first4=Mira|last5=Gruber|first5=Jonathan H.|last6=Newhouse|first6=Joseph P.|last7=Schneider|first7=Eric C.|last8=Wright|first8=Bill J.|last9=Zaslavsky|first9=Alan M.|date=2013-05-02|title=The Oregon Experiment — Effects of Medicaid on Clinical Outcomes|journal=New England Journal of Medicine|language=en|volume=368|issue=18|pages=1713–1722|doi=10.1056/NEJMsa1212321|issn=0028-4793|pmc=3701298|pmid=23635051}}</ref>，發現"Medicaid覆蓋率在頭兩年中並未讓受益者的身體健康產生顯著的改善" ，但確實"增加醫療衛生服務的使用率、提高[[糖尿病|糖尿病]]的檢測和後續處理、降低[[抑鬱症|抑鬱症]]的發生、並減輕患者的財務壓力。" 

研究發現在第一年：<ref>{{cite web|url=http://journalistsresource.org/studies/society/health/oregon-health-insurance-experiment/|title=Oregon Health Insurance Experiment: Evidence from the First Year|last=Olver|first=Christopher|date=2011-07-11|website=journalistsresource.org|accessdate=2020-07-26|archive-date=2014-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140818071446/http://journalistsresource.org/studies/society/health/oregon-health-insurance-experiment/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>
#有Medicaid覆蓋的人，醫院使用率增加30％，住院時間增加30％，使用療程增加45％；
#Medicaid的受益者，更有可能尋求預防護理。女性利用[[乳房攝影術|乳房攝影術]]的可能性增加60％，而作[[膽固醇|膽固醇]]檢查的，總體而言增加20％。
#就健康結果作自我報告而言，受益者與把自身健康報告為"好"、"非常好"、或"優秀"的可能性增加有關聯-總體上，比平均水準高約25％；
#受益者被檢出患有抑鬱症的可能性約低10％。
#會發生災難性醫療支出（費用超過收入的30％）的患者減少。
#受益者將需要貸款，或者放棄支付醫療費用帳單的可能性降低一半。<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.economist.com/blogs/democracyinamerica/2013/05/medicaid|title=More study needed|date=2013-05-06|journal=The Economist|access-date=2017-06-27|archive-date=2018-04-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180413124618/https://www.economist.com/blogs/democracyinamerica/2013/05/medicaid|dead-url=no}}</ref>

這些研究激起支持擴大Medicaid覆蓋的一方，<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2012/06/what-actually-happens-when-you-expand-medicaid-as-obamacare-does/258989/|title=What Actually Happens When You Expand Medicaid, as Obamacare Does?|last=Fung|first=Brian|date=2012-06-26|website=The Atlantic|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-18|archive-date=2019-04-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418190759/https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2012/06/what-actually-happens-when-you-expand-medicaid-as-obamacare-does/258989/|dead-url=no}}</ref>和反對的財政保守主義者（質疑擴展花費太大）的另一方之間的辯論。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/theapothecary/2013/05/02/oregon-study-medicaid-had-no-significant-effect-on-health-outcomes-vs-being-uninsured/|title=Oregon Study: Medicaid 'Had No Significant Effect' On Health Outcomes vs. Being Uninsured|last=Roy|first=Avik|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-04-18|archive-date=2019-04-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418190755/https://www.forbes.com/sites/theapothecary/2013/05/02/oregon-study-medicaid-had-no-significant-effect-on-health-outcomes-vs-being-uninsured/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

